T cells. This blocks the costimulatory signal required for full T cell activation, leading to reduced T cell proliferation and activity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEtanercept\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a tumour necrosis factor inhibitor, not involved in CD80/CD86 binding\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBelimumab\u003C/strong\u003E - This targets B lymphocyte stimulator, not CD80/CD86\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnakinra\u003C/strong\u003E - This is an interleukin-1 receptor antagonist, not involved in CD80/CD86 binding\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERituximab\u003C/strong\u003E - This targets CD20 on B cells, not CD80/CD86\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Abatacept is a fusion protein that binds to CD80 and CD86 on antigen-presenting cells, inhibiting T cell activation.","CD80 and CD86 are costimulatory molecules necessary for full T cell activation.","Blocking the interaction between CD80/CD86 and CD28 on T cells prevents the second signal required for T cell activation."],"references":["Padda IS, Goyal A. Leflunomide. 2023 Jun 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491731","Tian H, Cronstein BN. Understanding the mechanisms of action of methotrexate: implications for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis. Bull NYU Hosp Jt Dis. 2007;65(3):168-73. PMID: 17922664","Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing